1. sudo raspi-config
	- Expend Filesystem
	- Boot Options
		- B2 Console Autologin
	- Internationalisation Options
		- Change Timezone : Asia -> Seoul
		- Change Keyboard Layout : Generic 105-key -> Other -> Korean -> Korean(104...) -> default -> default -> default
	- Enable Camera : enable
	- Advanced Options
		- Hostname : R01 or R02 ...... R06
		- I2C : enable
	
2. update
	- sudo apt-get update
	- sudo apt-get upgrade
	
3. driver
	- url (https://www.raspberrypi.org/forums/viewtopic.php?f=28&t=122695)
		1) wget https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/80256631/8812au-4.1.7-v7-817.tar.gz
		2) tar xzf 8812au-4.1.7-v7-817.tar.gz
		3) ./install.sh
		
4. get source
	- git clone git://git.drogon.net/wiringPi
		1) cd wiringPi
		2) ./build
		3) gpio -v
	- git clone https://github.com/waroid/waroid.git
	
5. hostapd, dhcp
	- url (https://learn.adafruit.com/setting-up-a-raspberry-pi-as-a-wifi-acess-point/install-software)
	- url (http://elinux.org/RPI-Wireless-Hotspot)

7. Piborg
	- url (https://www.piborg.org/picoborgrev/install)


8. etc
	- sudo apt-get netcat-openbsd libncurses5-dev
	- /etc/inittab -> comment ttyAMA0

9. build and install
	- make rebuild
	- sudo make install
	- modified /etc/rc.local

* waroid/config folder
